  "message": "\ud83d\udc1b fix: make GitHub icon clickable to open GitHub repo\n\nThe GitHub icon in the navbar was only a dropdown trigger - clicking it\ndid nothing unless you selected a dropdown item. Now clicking the icon\ndirectly opens the kubestellar/kubestellar GitHub repo in a new tab.\n\nThe dropdown arrow still opens the dropdown menu with Star/Fork/Watch options.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nSigned-off-by: Andrew Anderson <andy@clubanderson.com>",
